The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA) tasks, which involve both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for VQA tasks, which involves tensor-based decomposition and low-rank matrix-based decomposition, indicating that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
